# Documentation updates

On **any** addition, change, or removal of functionality — update the corresponding documents in the same PR/commit.

## Checklist

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New feature / behavior change | `docs/SPECIFICATION.md` (requirements + acceptance criteria) |
| New plugin or Solidtime API endpoint | `docs/SOLIDTIME_API.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| New/changed UI component | `docs/UI.md` |
| New package, data flow change | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| New build command, dependency | `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md` |
| Overview feature change | `README.md` |
| New pattern from a reference plugin | `REFERENCE_PLUGINS.md` (feature → file matrix) |
| New Mattermost API/hooks | `docs/mattermost/` (if needed) |

## Rules

- Do not leave documentation stale — it is the contract for future development
- Add an acceptance criterion in `SPECIFICATION.md` for each new feature
- Future functionality outside scope goes in the "Future functionality" section (`SPECIFICATION.md`)
- When a backlog item is implemented, move it to the main specification and remove it from the backlog section

## Example

Adding time entry editing:
1. `SPECIFICATION.md` — description, acceptance criterion
2. `UI.md` — edit icon, modal window
3. `SOLIDTIME_API.md` — `PUT /time-entries/{id}`
4. `ARCHITECTURE.md` — new proxy endpoint
